## Natural Fancy Pink Cushion Cut Diamond — Understanding the Grades

The GIA grading scale for pink diamonds is not a simple spectrum from light to dark. It has modifiers — secondary hues — that change the appearance and price dramatically.

### What "Fancy Brown Pink" Actually Looks Like

"Fancy Brown Pink" is a GIA grade with brown as the secondary hue and pink as the primary. In practice, these stones can range from a warm salmon/rose to a brownish peach. The [1ct Fancy Brown Pink VS2 at $38,006](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-20891251?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is a genuinely pink stone — but the brown modifier is visible.

Compare that to the [1.02ct Fancy Brownish Pink SI2 at $9,488](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-28204124?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). "Brownish Pink" means pink is the secondary hue — the stone reads as primarily brown with pink tones. This is why it costs $9,488 instead of $38,006 for the same carat weight.

The hierarchy of natural pink cushion grades from most to least expensive:
1. **Fancy Vivid Pink** — almost impossible to find in retail; auction-only at 6-figure premiums per carat
2. **Fancy Intense Pink** — [$339,521 for 1.50ct](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-28823852?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational), [$400,060 for 1.00ct](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-23341915?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
3. **Fancy Purplish Pink** — [$112,324 for 1.13ct](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-9345528?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
4. **Fancy Brown Pink** — [$38,006 for 1ct](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-20891251?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at VS2
5. **Fancy Brownish Pink** — [$9,488 for 1.02ct](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-28204124?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational); [$61,311 for 2.02ct](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-25377484?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

The modifier matters more than carat weight at small sizes. A 1ct Fancy Intense Pink costs 10× more than a 1ct Fancy Brown Pink — and the difference is visible to the naked eye.

### Why "Fancy Brownish Orangy Pink" at $70,811 Costs More Than "Fancy Brown Pink" at $38,006

This seems counterintuitive. Orangy Pink should be worse than Brown Pink, right?

Not in natural fancy diamonds. The [1.18ct Fancy Brownish Orangy Pink at $70,811](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-20848653?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) costs nearly double the 1ct Fancy Brown Pink because of the rarity of orangy hues in pink diamonds. Orangy Pink is a distinct and collectible hue that commands premiums beyond standard brown modifiers. Fancy color diamond pricing is not always rational by grade name alone — it reflects rarity of the specific color combination.

