## Final Verdict — Best For

**Best for engagement ring buyers:** [5ct IGI Fancy Vivid Pink VS1 lab — $3,045](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-29194960?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). This is the pink cushion cut diamond that most buyers are actually looking for — vivid color, large size, accessible price. Set it in rose gold and it's extraordinary.

**Best for natural pink buyers on a budget:** [1.02ct GIA Fancy Brownish Pink SI2 — $9,488](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-28204124?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). This is the true natural pink entry point. Understand that "brownish pink" means brown is the stronger hue — watch the video carefully before buying.

**Best for true natural pink:** [1ct GIA Fancy Brown Pink VS2 — $38,006](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-20891251?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Pure pink with brown modifier — genuinely pink to the eye, GIA certified, eye-clean clarity. This is where natural pink starts looking like what buyers expect.

**Best for collectors and investors:** [1.13ct GIA Fancy Purplish Pink SI1 — $112,324](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-9345528?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Purplish pink with no brown modifier is a collector grade. Stones with this profile are in demand at auction and among private collectors globally, especially post-Argyle closure.

---

## Expert Summary

Pink cushion cut diamonds split into two entirely different markets. Natural fancy pink cushion cuts start at [$9,488 for Fancy Brownish Pink](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-28204124?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and reach [$979,347 for Fancy Intense Purplish Pink](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-21749730?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — the price curve is driven by GIA color modifier, not carat weight.

Lab-grown pink cushion cuts make Fancy Vivid Pink accessible for the first time in diamond history. A [5ct IGI Fancy Vivid Pink VS1 at $3,045](https://www.bluenile.com/colored-diamond-details/pink-29194960?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) has a higher color grade than most natural pink diamonds ever certified. The Lab Sovereign has taken over the retail pink diamond category — and that is objectively good for buyers.

The Colour Cut Advantage makes cushion the correct shape choice for pink regardless of origin. Larger facets pool body color. The world's most famous pink diamonds are cushion cuts for this reason. Don't buy pink in a round brilliant.

Argyle mine closed in 2020. Certified Argyle pink cushion cuts now trade as collectibles with premiums above comparable GIA stones. If you encounter one, the Argyle certificate adds real value — but there is no new supply.

